article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 68, Tennessee State 65
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Matt Witt hit a 3-pointer with 5.4 seconds left Monday night to lift Eastern Kentucky to a 68-65 win over Tennessee State. Tennessee State (4-17, 4-7 Ohio Valley Conference) had a chance to tie the score on their last possession, but Garrett Richardson's 3-pointer from the right side bounced off the front of the rim as time expired. The Colonels (9-12, 4-6) snapped a three-game losing streak. Tennessee State led by four with two minutes left, but Eastern scored the last four points of the contest in a game that featured nine ties and 14 lead changes. Jon Bentley led Eastern with 22 points on 9-of-11 shooting from the field. Ben Rushing came off the bench and scored 13 points, while Witt followed with 11 points. Tennessee State's Bruce Price led all players with 25 points, 18 in the first half. Price had four of his team's eight 3-pointers. Richardson scored 17 points and Roshaun Bowens added 10 for the Tigers.
